						               													<description>Conspiracy is an upcoming card game released in spring 2023, on Kickstarter. It is a fun, fast-paced tableau-builder for those who wanna try what it's like to be a conspiracy theory believer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chose your core conspiracy (card) and build your unique theory around it by winning news (cards) and explaining how those fit your theory. (Don't worry explanation is optional and you can skip it by playing the game in Flat Earther variant.) Each conspiracy card gives a special ability to its believer. Use it wisely to become more influential than your rivals and their childish tales.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Conspiracy, each player acts simultaneously during the two rounds of a turn. There are three types of action they can choose from: action card drawing, playing an action card, and flipping a news card. Action cards give you some useful abilities and influence among the believers. The most influential wins the actual news (card) at the end of the turn. By your clairvoyance ability, you can flip your news cards to see the hidden message between the lines and get a useful bonus.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player wins and the game ends when any player reaches the given number of followers and is able to keep them until the end of the turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Conspiracy offers a cooperative and a solo mode as well where you can work together (or alone) to uncover the shadow government before it's too late. Merge your conspiracy cards to the ultimate great grandfathers of all conspiracy theories and play action cards side by side against the shadow government cards to win the actual news (card), protect your theory and your hands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In cooperative mode, the game ends when the players reach the given number of followers and keep them until the end of the turn or when the shadow government deck is depleted.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The core mechanics of the game are: hand management, flipping a card, bid, tableau building, variable player powers, and narrative building.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
